\f0\fs42\fsmilli21333 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0 Design \f1\fs24 \cf3 \ \pard\pardeftab720\sl360\sa240\partightenfactor0
\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf3 Provide a design for part of a payments API. A list of payments might look like \cf4 http://mockbin.org/bin/41ca3269-d8c4-4063-9fd5-f306814ff03f\cf3 . \f1\fs24 \
\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 Design requirements: \f1\fs24 \ \pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl360\sa293\partightenfactor0 \ls1\ilvl0 \f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext \uc0\u8226 }\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0 API should be RESTFUL \f1 \uc0\u8232 \ \ls1\ilvl0 \f2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext \uc0\u8226 }\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0 API should be able to: \f1 \uc0\u8232 \ \pard\pardeftab720\sl340\sa240\partightenfactor0
\f3 \cf3 o \f2 Fetch a payment resource\uc0\u8232 \f3 o \f2 Create, update and delete a payment resource \f3 o \f2 List a collection of payment resources\uc0\u8232 \f3 o \f2 Persist resource state (e.g. to a database) \f1\fs24 \ \pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa240\partightenfactor0
\f0\fs34\fsmilli17333 \cf2 Example use case: \f1\fs24 \cf3 \ \pard\pardeftab720\sl360\sa240\partightenfactor0
\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf3 As an example, a JavaScript client should be able to call the API and list a collection of payments (building a client is outside the scope of this exercise however). \f1\fs24 \ }
